07/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- In a special message to Prime Minister Fatos Nano, US Vice President Dick Cheney praised Albania's support in the fight against terrorism.
The letter said that US President George W. Bush's administration is determined to face the threats posed to the United States and its allies, including Albania.
Cheney also encouraged Albania to continue its progress toward NATO membership, stressing the country's role in regional stability.
(ATA - 06/11/02)
